<p>During a recent review of all our disused assets, the Commercial Development team identified seven stations and one deep level shelter with great commercial potential.</p>
<p>The review also allowed us to establish that:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Few are complete stations and no site is disused or abandoned</li>
    <li>Most, directly lead to live operational railway and continue to perform important operational functions, e.g. maintenance and emergency access</li>
    <li>Each location presents a unique combination of commercial opportunity and operational constraint</li>
</ul>
<p>
We commissioned Carmody Groarke, a firm of architects with experience in this area, to conduct a commercial feasibility study at the disused Down Street station. This study aimed to:</p>
<ul>
    <li>Identify potential secondary revenue opportunities </li>
    <li>Create a methodology, or assessment template, which could be adapted and applied to other sites in the future</li>
</ul>
<p>
The study concluded that the Down Street station site had many attributes which collectively outweighed its constraints. As a result, we're now seeking commercial proposals for this site.</p>
<p>Our digital brochure provides information about the Downs Street site and the tender process. Find out more: </p>
